ception`, changed behavior, or new exceptions.\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:15:The existing `fix_javac_fail` workflow handles compilation failures. Runtime failures should use the same operational model, but with runtime-focused prompt wording, separate strategy names, separate metrics, and a separate PR label.\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:62:1. Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<library>` to collect failure output.\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:67:6. Send subsequent failure output back to the agent until success or `max-test-iterations`.\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:72:- javac fixes uses compilation-failure wording and writes `fix_javac_fail.json`.\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:73:- java fixes runs uses runtime-failure wording and writes `fix_java_run_fail.json`.\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:123:- Fix the runtime test failures for library version `{updated_library}`. Test was initially written for version `{old_version}`.\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:131:- Look for API changes, including renamed methods, changed signatures, removed classes, changed behavior, or new exceptions that explain the runtime failures.\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:132:- Stop inspecting sources once you understand the cause of each failure. Then make the minimal edit.\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:161:    \\\"max-test-iterations\\\": 5,\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:162:    \\\"max-iterations\\\": 2,\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:163:    \\\"max-class-test-iterations\\\": 2,\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:172:`forge_metadata.py` dispatches Java version-bump failures through the unified entry point:\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:202:When the runtime test failure occurs under `nativeTest` (rather than plain\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:215:    Verify -- fail --> Codex[run_codex_metadata_fix<br/>with output_dir + result.failure]\\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:228:  partial) plus the `result.failure` d