L.md:92:  reviewers and report the failure explicitly.\\n./skills/ipr/SKILL.md:104:- any reviewer or linking failures\\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:102:- CI failures point to a real regression or invalid update.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-java-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR described as `fixes-java-run-fail` or one that fixes Java/JVM runtime test failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the Java runtime fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair tests, dependencies, or narrow runtime setup after an existing library version compiles, but the JVM-based test fails when it runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to restore Java runtime behavior for the new version while preserving meaningful test and dynamic-access coverage.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:50:   - Confirm the edit addresses the actual JVM runtime failure, such as changed runtime behavior, missing test resources, service loading changes, dependency conflicts, classpath/module issues, initialization order, changed exception types, or changed API semantics that only fail during execution.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:78:   - If current-defaults and future-defaults lanes both run, both should pass unless the PR clearly targets only one failing lane and the other failure is unrelated infrastructure noise.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:85:- The PR is scoped to the target existing library and the Java runtime failure it fixes.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:97:- CI failures indicate the Java runtime problem is not actually fixed.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:113:- For swallowed exceptions: say that catching or ignoring the failing exception hides the runtime failure instead of proving the library behavior works.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:115:- For unverified `catch (Error)`: say that dynamic class loading tests should verify Native Image failures with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` and re-throw any other error.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:125:- Bad runtime repair that swallows the failure:\\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:21:- Require reported dynamic-access coverage above 20% when there are dynamic-access calls to cover. Use the exploded stats files under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` when available, and block the PR when dynamic-access coverage is 20% or lower or the PR provides no credible dynamic-access coverage evidence for non-zero dynamic-access calls.\\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:22:- Treat dynamic-access coverage counts as a minimum gate, not complete metadata evidence. They can miss metadata required through downstream libraries, so do not use high coverage alone to prove that the submitted metadata is complete or necessary.\\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:23:- Treat `0/0` dynamic-access coverage as a valid no-calls case, not as failed coverage. Do not reject a PR only because the exploded stats report `0/0` dynamic-access calls while the PR adds metadata; those stats can miss metadata required through downstream libraries.\\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:63:   - Confirm reported dynamic-access coverage is above 20% when the stats include dynamic-access calls.\\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:90:  - Reported dynamic-access coverage is 20% or lower for non-zero dynamic-access calls, absent for claimed dynamic-access behavior, or not credible from the diff.\\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:98:- For unverified `catch (Error)`: say that dynamic class loading tests should verify Native Image failures with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` and re-throw any other error.\\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:101:- For insufficient dynamic-access coverage: say that new-library PRs need dynamic-access coverage above 20% when there are dynamic-access calls to cover, and ask for stronger tests or refreshed coverage evidence.\\n./forge/prompt_templates/fix-java-run/initial-with-sources.md:2:- Fix the runtime test failures for library version `{updated_library}`. Test was initially written for version `{old_version}`.\\n./forge/prompt_templates/fix-java-run/initial-with-sources.md:10:- Look for API changes, including renamed methods, changed signatures, removed classes, changed behavior, or new exceptions that explain the runtime failures.\\n./forge/prompt_templates/fix-java-run/initial-with-sources.md:11:- Stop inspecting sources once you understand the cause of each failure. Then make the minimal edit.\\n./forge/prompt_templates/fix-java-run/initial-with-sources.md:16:- Every individual test must complete in under 60 seconds. If the failure is a timeout or deadlock, use the provided stacktrace/thread dump to replace unbounded waits with bounded waits and close all clients, servers, executors, and other background resources.\\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:16:1. Reproduce the failure:\\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:67:- If failures look unrelated or tooling looks inconsistent, verify both `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME` point to a compatible GraalVM JDK distribution.\\n./skills/README.md:27:It covers compile-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the compile fix, preserve meaningful tests, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n./skills/README.md:32:It covers JVM runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the Java runtime fix, preserve meaningful tests and assertions, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n./skills/README.md:37:It covers native-image runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: verify the native path is fixed rather than skipped, keep metadata and test changes scoped, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept fixes that hide the failing native path by skipping assertions, skipping native-image runtime execution, or weakening the test until the failure disappears.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:48:   - Confirm the metadata or test change matches the observed native runtime failure, such as missing reflection, resources, proxies, serialization constructors, JNI access, or class initialization behavior.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:55:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:75:   - If current-defaults and future-defaults lanes both run, both should pass unless the PR clearly targets only one failing lane and the other failure is unrelated infrastructure noise.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:82:- The PR is scoped to the target existing library and the native-image runtime failure it fixes.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:93:- Metadata additions are unrelated to the failure or affect other libraries without justification.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:94:- CI failures indicate the native-image runtime problem is not actually fixed.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:40:     Do not close those PRs for CI failure alone.\\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:188:- any verification failures that still need manual follow-up\\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration-update.md:12:Full dynamic-access coverage report, all classes with uncovered call sites:\\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:12:Full dynamic-access coverage report, all classes with uncovered call sites:\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:49:   - Confirm the edit addresses the actual Java compilation failure, such as renamed classes, changed method signatures, module boundaries, annotation processors, or dependency coordinates.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:75:   - If current-defaults and future-defaults lanes both run, both should pass unless the PR clearly targets only one failing lane and the other failure is unrelated infrastructure noise.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:82:- The PR is scoped to the target existing library and the compile failure it fixes.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:94:- CI failures indicate the compile problem is not actually fixed.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:111:- For unverified `catch (Error)`: say that dynamic class loading tests should verify Native Image failures with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` and re-throw any other error.\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:38:### Fix javac test failures for a new library version\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:184:### Pipeline: Fix javac test failures + PR creation\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:293:      global_iterations=3,\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:295:      strategy_name=\\\"basic_iterative\\\",\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:366:    \\\"max-test-iterations\\\": 10,\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:384:failure output in normal prompt templates.\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:401:       REQUIRED_PARAMS = [\\\"max-test-iterations\\\"]\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:449:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:85:2. **Fix `javac` failures** raised by a library version bump.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:86:3. **Fix native-image runtime failures** raised by a library version bump.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:275:- GitHub issues for new-version compatibility failures, one per `(library, version)`.\\n./docs/CI.md:40:  - Uses: [`fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) plus [`generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\\n./human-intervention-logs/org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-xc:1.6.9/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log:29:Find the repository URL, the sources URL, the test suite URL, the documentation URL, and a concise two-sentence explanation for the following library: org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-xc:1.6.9\\n./human-intervention-logs/org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-xc:1.6.9/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log:842:/usr/bin/bash -lc './gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-xc:1.6.9 --stacktrace' in /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_rep